page.content: Travelling east on the Tincleton-Dorchester road we encounter the site of Heedle Williams pond which is exceedingly difficult to find as it is overgrown with braken. To the north of the road is Duddle Heath which rises up from the road and is covered in many tumuli. The heath is covered in heather and braken and is broken in the middle by Duddle plantation which is a man-made wood of mixed trees. Furthe east along the road is a Georgian house -Norris mill. Next to Norris Mill is Lower Norris mill which is a farm ,owning 130 acres of dairyland. The road goes downhill in an easterly direction with houses at irregular intervals.
